# Development Rules

## Development Overview

### Technology Stack
- **Next.js 15** with App Router
- **React 19** with latest features
- **TypeScript** for type safety
- **Tailwind CSS** for styling
- **Prisma ORM** for database operations
- **NextAuth.js v4** for authentication

### Development Principles
- **Type-safe development** with TypeScript
- **Component-based architecture** with React
- **Clean code** principles and best practices
- **Consistent coding** standards across the project

## Code Organization

### Project Structure
```
src/
├── app/                    # Next.js App Router
│   ├── api/               # API routes
│   ├── auth/              # Authentication pages
│   ├── admin/             # Admin pages
│   ├── superadmin/        # SuperAdmin pages
│   ├── voter/             # Voter interface
│   └── public/            # Public pages
├── components/            # Reusable components
├── lib/                  # Utility libraries
├── types/                # TypeScript definitions
└── generated/            # Generated Prisma client
```

### File Naming Conventions
- **PascalCase** for components: `Button.tsx`, `ElectionList.tsx`
- **camelCase** for utilities: `prisma.ts`, `constants.ts`
- **kebab-case** for pages: `election-status.tsx`, `ballot-form.tsx`
- **snake_case** for database: `migration.sql`, `schema.prisma`

### Component Organization
- **One component per file** for clarity
- **Index files** for barrel exports
- **Component folders** for complex components
- **Shared components** in `/components/ui`

## TypeScript Standards

### Type Definitions
- **Strict TypeScript** configuration
- **No `any` types** without justification
- **Proper interface** definitions for all data structures
- **Generic types** for reusable components

### Type Organization
```typescript
// src/types/index.ts - Barrel exports
export * from "./auth";
export * from "./api";
export * from "./components";
export * from "./database";

// src/types/auth.ts - Authentication types
export interface User {
  id: string;
  email: string;
  name: string;
  role: UserRole;
  isApproved: boolean;
  organization?: Organization;
}

// src/types/api.ts - API types
export interface ApiResponse<T = any> {
  success: boolean;
  data?: T;
  message?: string;
  error?: string;
  statusCode: number;
}
```

### Type Safety Guidelines
- **Type all function parameters** and return values
- **Use union types** for better type safety
- **Implement proper error types** for error handling
- **Type all API responses** and requests

